sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin User
    participant UM as UserManagement
    participant Confirm as ConfirmModal
    participant Hook as useUserManagement
    participant API as useDeleteUser
    participant Backend as Backend API
    
    Note over Admin,Backend: Delete User Flow
    
    Admin->>UM: Click Delete button on user
    UM->>Hook: handleDelete(user)
    Hook->>Hook: openDeleteModal(user)
    Hook->>UM: Set isDeleteOpen=true<br/>selectedUserForDelete=user
    UM->>Confirm: Render ConfirmModal
    
    Note over Admin,Backend: Confirmation Dialog
    
    Confirm->>Admin: Display confirmation message:<br/>"Delete user email@example.com?"
    
    alt Admin cancels
        Admin->>Confirm: Click Cancel
        Confirm->>Hook: closeDeleteModal()
        Hook->>UM: Set isDeleteOpen=false
        UM->>Confirm: Unmount modal
    else Admin confirms
        Admin->>Confirm: Click Delete button
        Confirm->>Hook: handleConfirmDelete()
        Hook->>API: deleteUserMutation.execute()
        API->>Backend: DELETE /users/:id
        Backend-->>API: Success response
        API-->>Hook: Delete successful
        Hook->>Hook: closeDeleteModal()
        Hook->>UM: Set isDeleteOpen=false
        Hook->>UM: refetchUsers()
        UM->>UM: Execute GET /users query
        UM->>UM: Re-render UserTable<br/>(user removed from list)
        Confirm->>Confirm: Unmount modal
    end

